All Classes

Class Description
AllocatedProteinEntry
Internal object representation of a protein that was allocated to a single FeatureEntry.
AminoacidVariantAnnotationEntry
Object used to store annotations for a single amino-acid variant.
Bio
Comprises static methods used to solve specifically bioinformatics problems.
Bio.GLOBAL_SEQUENCE_ALIGNMENT_MARGIN_GAP_MODES
Enum to store different modes to handle prefix gaps for global sequence alignment.
CL
This class comprises static methods used for calling command line commands.
CLIParameters
Interface for command line interface argument parsers.
CLIParametersInferSequences
Parses command line interface arguments for the `MUSIAL inferSequences` module.
CLIParametersUpdateVDict
Parses command line interface arguments for the `MUSIAL updateVDict` module.
FastaContainer
Represents the entry from a `.fasta` file.
FeatureEntry
Internal representation of a reference sequence location that is subject to analysis.
IO
This class comprises static methods used for reading and writing files.
Logging
This class comprises static methods used for status logging.
Musial
Main class of MUSIAL (MUlti Sample varIant AnaLysis), a tool to calculate SNV, gene, and whole genome alignments, together with other relevant statistics based on vcf files.
MusialBioException
Exception thrown if any data generation or storage process is incorrect in the context of the software, e.g. gene features with negative lengths.
MusialCLException
Exception thrown if any error occurs during parsing and validating the user specified command line arguments.
MusialIntegrityException
Exception thrown if any data manipulation procedure is not logical in the context of the software, for example the assignment of a protein resource to a whole genome reference feature.
MusialIOException
Exception thrown to indicate an error during I/O operations of MUSIAL internal methods.
MusialModules
Enum specifying modules of MUSIAL to choose from.
NucleotideVariantAnnotationEntry
Object used to store annotations for a single nucleotide variant.
ProteoformEntry
Represents a proteoform, i.e. a set of single-position amino-acid variants (may include inserted and deleted positions), wrt. a FeatureEntry.allocatedProtein.
SampleAnalyzerRunnable
Implementation of the Runnable interface to analyze a sample.
SampleEntry
Internal representation of a sample that is subject to analysis.
SnpEffAnnotator
Runs a local installation of SnpEff via command line.
Validation
This class comprises static methods used for validating input data.
VariantsDictionary
Main data structure to store information about variants.
VariantsDictionaryFactory
Comprises static methods to analyze samples in order to build a new variants dictionary.
VariantsDictionaryParameters
Stores the main parameters used for variant filtering for a VariantsDictionary.
